::
++  find-impl
  |=  {a/(map @sd record:yint) p/$-(record:yint ?)}
  |-
  ^-  (unit @sd)
  ?~  a  ~
  ?:  (p q.n.a)  `p.n.a
  =+  lhs=$(a l.a)
  ?~  lhs
    =+  rhs=$(a r.a)
    ?~  rhs
      ~
    rhs
  lhs

:: Performs a depth first walk of the tree returning the first index to match
:: the passed in predicate. Returns ++nothing:yint if nothing matches.
++  find-record
  |=  p/$-(record:yint ?)
  ^-  @sd
  =+  x=(find-impl records.db p)
  ?~  x  nothing:yint
  (need x)

